WEBVTT

00:07.918 --> 00:09.268
<i>My name is Melinda Gordon.</i>

00:11.968 --> 00:12.968
<i>I just got married,</i>

00:13.155 --> 00:14.555
<i>just moved to a small town,</i>

00:14.732 --> 00:16.332
<i>just opened up an antique shop.</i>

00:16.853 --> 00:18.153
<i>I might be just like you.</i>

00:19.637 --> 00:21.604
<i>Except from the time that I was a little girl,</i>

00:21.605 --> 00:23.505
<i>I knew that I could talk to the dead.</i>

00:25.122 --> 00:26.213
<i>It's all right, honey.</i>

00:26.214 --> 00:28.551
<i>Earthbound spirits, my grandmother called them,</i>

00:28.558 --> 00:29.940
<i>the ones who have not crossed over</i>

00:29.941 --> 00:34.192
<i>because they have unfinished business with the living, and they come to me for help.</i>

00:35.065 --> 00:36.163
<i>To tell you my story,</i>

00:36.670 --> 00:38.028
<i>I have to tell you theirs.</i>

00:44.749 --> 00:45.822
Andrea. Melinda.

00:47.427 --> 00:48.323
Sit over there.

00:49.268 --> 00:50.162
Oh.

00:55.725 --> 00:56.482
Hello.

00:56.497 --> 00:58.220
Welcome to room 3's talent night.

00:58.757 --> 01:00.532
One of our students, Dillon Cho,

01:00.876 --> 01:03.142
has written a very imaginative play.

01:03.745 --> 01:06.960
We hope you enjoy room 3's production of

01:07.436 --> 01:09.411
"Ghost at the crossing."

01:14.835 --> 01:17.180
You know what they say: "Write what you know."

01:20.276 --> 01:25.121
I'm so bored. My dad has gone away, and my mom's too busy to even talk to me.

01:25.706 --> 01:26.602
Hi.

01:26.735 --> 01:27.630
Wanna play?

01:27.765 --> 01:28.663
Who are you?

01:28.838 --> 01:29.730
I'm a ghost.

01:29.795 --> 01:30.763
No way.

01:31.895 --> 01:33.522
Wanna come to the railroad tracks?

01:33.527 --> 01:34.922
I'm really not supposed to.

01:35.075 --> 01:35.970
Oh, come on.

01:36.386 --> 01:39.352
We can put pennies on the tracks and watch 'em get squished.

01:39.356 --> 01:41.021
Melinda, help me.

01:47.545 --> 01:49.390
Scene 2: The railroad tracks.

